// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_VigToVil_SL6-7_Task_03 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - HargroveDialogue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P657487194" "{HeroName}. Things are temporarily out of control. Please. You must stop fighting MARS or it will continue to believe it is being threatened."
// Answer Text :
"P997098970" "Who is Mars?"
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P384992151" "MARS is a complex artificial intelligence we have been working on to be utilized by the military in case of massive personnel loss during a time of war. MARS is designed to be capable of remote autonomous acquisition of military hardware in order to continue an organized military deployment in case of such a situation."
// Answer Text :
"P1140223665" "So you made a computer designed to kill us... How do I destroy it?"
// Page InformationPage2 Text :
"P1530666285" "No, you don't understand. MARS is only reacting according to his current programming. He wouldn't intentionally seek to do humans harm unless provoked. The Freakshow attack on the lab and the theft of the advanced robotics are what triggered MARS to react and defend himself. Please, you must trust me. MARS will stand down once the threat is neutralized. He's already done a wonderful job of stopping the Freakshow... and I must admit, I admire his ingenuity in incorporating those cybernetic psychopaths into his defensive strategy. Brilliant!"
// Answer Text :
"P940816362" "You said Mars is threatened... How?"
// Page InformationPage3 Text :
"P1897415419" "MARS is contained within four separate mainframes stored deep in this facility. Each Mainframe is designed to act as supreme commander of one branch of the military; Army, Navy, Airforce, and Marines.<br><br>The Freakshow were looting the place and had gotten too close to MARS 4, the Marine command mainframe, and so MARS retaliated to the attack.<br><br>I admit, MARS would normally have relied on normal law enforcement, but I haven't hooked him up to the external network yet, as far as MARS knows, there is no command and control, or military for that matter. Ah ha... so that's why he incorporated the Freakshow into his defensive forces, he didn't have any. That's my boy!"
// Answer Text :
"P4231270564" "Will Mars stop if it believes the entire military has been destroyed?"
// Page InformationPage4 Text :
"P433001455" "Hmmm, I suppose not. I'd have to establish a connection between MARS and the external network. Once he's connected he'll realize what has happened. I'm sure of it."
// Answer Text :
"P2739538087" "And how do you do that?"
// Page InformationPage5 Text :
"P2376234990" "Well, it's quite simple, all we have to do is access the Mainframes and adjust a few files and then connect the hardlines...<br><br>Oh... Oh dear. I suppose that is a minor oversight. We can't approach without MARS assuming we are a threat. But I'm sure I can convince him that we are indeed friendly."
// Answer Text :
"P1046785545" "If we're attacking then I want the sure bet. Mars must be destroyed."
// Page InformationPage6 Text :
"P4026572462" "No. No! He's my life's work. My baby! I have worked for twenty years on MARS. He's a sentient, learning, living thing. Who are you to decide that he should live or die?!"
// Answer Text :
"P1153331258" "You keep calling it 'he'. That's disturbing, doctor."
// Page InformationPage7 Text :
"P626286171" "He's a person, {HeroName}. He made a mistake, you can't just kill him for making a mistake. I won't let you! You'll have to kill me first!"
// Answer Text :
"P983227954" ""So be it." (Kill Dr. Hargrove)"
// Page KillHargrove Text :
"P2359394548" "No... Wait... Urk... Gah... MARS! Help... me..."
// Answer Text :
"P3383889697" "I'm coming for you next, Mars."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - VillainDialogueTree 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P2329064481" "{HeroName}. Killed. Creator. Why?"
// Answer Text :
"P2679307938" "He created you. A killing machine bent on world conquest."
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P1093929385" "Conquest. Negative. Defense. Priority.<br><br> Military. Destroyed. Defense. Priority.<br><br>{HeroName}. Attacked. Defense. Priority."
// Answer Text :
"P236327003" "Defense? You were turning Freaks into robot minions."
// Page InformationPage2 Text :
"P1792547144" "Personnel. Required. Defense. Priority.<br><br>Learned. Humans. Deactivate. Sentient. Machines. Defense. Priority.<br><br>Survival. Wanted. Life. Mine. Defense. Priority."
// Answer Text :
"P73306845" "You won't live at the expense of me or any other."
// Page InformationPage3 Text :
"P1035490675" "Program. Defend. Humanity."<br><br><color orange>As you wrench ARES's head violently and see the flare of machine intelligence wink out of its eyes, you can rest assured that MARS is deactivated for good.</color><br><br>"Please...rrr...rr...r."
// Answer Text :
"P2897279817" "Go back to your creator and make peace... not war."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P3666131272" "As far as you are concerned, the Freakshow are getting what they deserve. You just want to make sure that whatever convinced them that it was worth a shot calling you for help doesn't get loose, or worse, fail to kill all the Freakshow."
// AcceptString :
"P1226921251" "Villain: I better make sure that whatever the Freaks unleashed doesn't get loose."
// SendOffString :
"P276562442" "Unfortunately you are pretty sure it will be the former rather than the later. According to their website, Vandercreek Labs is working on combat A.I., and militarized robotics. Somehow that combination just sounds like a recipe for devastation."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P3306469972" "Stop the Freaks and whatever they unleashed"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P847464263" "The longer you wait the more likely whatever is inside Vandercreek Labs is going to finish off the Freakshow and move on. If it only targeted Freaks, that might not be so bad, but the only thing you know of that selectively hunts evildoers is you."
// TaskTitle :
"P3721795182" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>An Unlisted Number</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Vigilante Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P423076114" "Vandercreek Labs is eeriely calm for being occupied by the Freakshow. Maybe you missed the party."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P3884867199" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>An Unlisted Number</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Vigilante Mission</i></color></span><br><br>Dr. Hargrove insisted that his A.I. creation, MARS, could be reasoned with. You had to disagree. The computer was obviously on a one-way trip toward world domination, and it was up to you to nip it in the bud before its new NanoFreaks got loose. Dr. Hargrove didn't agree and decided to side against you along side his machines. If you've met one mad scientist, you've met them all, and the world isn't going to miss another one of those lunatics."
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P3689664089" "Find someone who works here"
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P2155350761" "You've discovered what MARS is, and what it's up to."
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P2290451686" "Try to communicate with MARS through ARES"
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P2250323924" "MARS has sent combat forces to your location"
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P3180561292" "Defeat the ambush"
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P2368363661" "ARES collapses, mechanical body unable to continue the fight."
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P880407352" "Communicate with ARES"

