// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - Objective 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P3347874009" "Beautiful Annabella"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P2783095250" "Beautiful Annabella is a masterful villain who claims to have put her life of crime behind her. Based on her police record, you highly doubt that."
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P3155183045" "<shout>Darling? Achilles? {HeroName} if you've hurt them..."
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P3135353607" "... No! {HeroName}! You... You monster! How could you!? HOW COULD YOU!"
// Script Variable BOSS_75HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P776376589" "Why?! We did our time, we paid for our crimes? Can't you let the past be the past?"
// Script Variable BOSS_50HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P2351095988" "You took everything from me! EVERYTHING! My best friend! My lover! Everything!"
// Script Variable BOSS_25HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P195240744" "I will never forgive you! I will see you and everyone in this city who you ever cared about dead!"
// Script Variable Greeting :
"P3011679019" "I'll kill you.... *sniff*... I'll kill you..."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - TaskSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog :
"P3947846147" "Good intentions or not, nothing could ever undo the evil that Beautiful Annabella and her gang unleashed on the innocent. Their debt of vengeance is paid now, with their lives. Only the bitter sweet memories of lost loved ones will remain, for nobody mourns the passing of the wicked."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - ReturnSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// RandomFameString :
"P1774341909" "I heard that Beautiful Annabella's Carnival was cancelled. I was looking forward to it. A shame the charities won't benefit from the proceeds."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_VigToVil_SL6-7_Task_06 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - FoughtFirstHeroBoss 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P2721234686" "Jim Matherson"
// DetailString :
"P2782800394" "Jim Matherson just could not come to see how obvious it was that Steel Mountain was plotting to trap and kill him. He was determined to throw his life away in vehement support of a known criminal, and in doing so would have jeopardized the life of Sidewinder. You took it upon yourself to ensure Jim's death was a sacrifice, and not without meaning, so you killed him yourself and resolved to tell Sidewinder that Steel Mountain had killed him in order to make sure the same fate didn't befall her."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - FirstHeroBossDialogue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P2344382225" "I'm surprised to see you here, {HeroName}. I figured you thought Steel Mountain was irredeemable. I'm glad to see that you realized you were wrong."
// Answer Text :
"P1140694667" "Steel Mountain, is he here?"
// Page WorkingWithVillain Text :
"P265975862" "Yeah, he came in through the south entrance, Sidewinder from the northwest. I will say, I was a little shaky at first, but man, the intelligence he's provided has been dead on the money. He's been a real asset."
// Answer Text :
"P590130059" "Steel Mountain is leading you into a trap. I have sources..."
// Page IHaveProof Text :
"P1840653799" "Sources? You mean enemies that will say anything to see him taken down a notch. Seriously, {HeroName}, Steel Mountain has changed his ways, he's one of us now. Until you get some solid evidence there is no way that I'm taking that man's chance to redeem himself away from him."
// Answer Text :
"P3971659603" "Then you are already dead..."
// Page BetrayFirstHeroBoss Text :
"P550477144" "Dead? What are you talking about? Now wait a second..."
// Answer Text :
"P1440334563" "If you're to die then let it be to save someone else."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - SecondHeroBossDialogue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P3797542547" "Where did you come from, {HeroName}? Did Matherson send you? I haven't heard from him since I went radio silent."
// Answer Text :
"P738653082" "And you never will again, Steel Mountain killed him."
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P966779177" "What?! What are you talking about?"<br><br><color orange>Sidewinder speaks into her radio</color><br><br>"Sidewinder to Matherson, come in... Matherson, this is Sidewinder, over..."
// Answer Text :
"P3767113860" "I saw it with my own eyes, Steel Mountain played you."
// Page InformationPage2 Text :
"P1153446894" "Dammit... Dammit! I knew it... I knew that slimeball couldn't be trusted. Jim, you idiot, I told you but you wouldn't listen...<br><br>Alright, {HeroName}, we do this together. Steel Mountain is going to pay!"
// Answer Text :
"P1394901273" "Right, we can't let Matherson's death be for nothing."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P2552507525" "Steel Mountain has convinced Jim Matherson to team up with him in order to take on the Freakshow. You know he is leading Jack into a trap. It is bad enough that old gung ho Jim is falling into it, but Jack decided to recruit Sidewinder and bring her along as well. It's up to you to take Steel Mountain down and expose him for the villain he was and still is. You don't have much time to intercept Jim and prove to him what Steel Mountain is planning. Jim is an idiot, especially for dragging Sidewinder into this mess."
// AcceptString :
"P3211350967" "Save Jim Matherson and Sidewinder from Steel Mountain's trap."
// SendOffString :
"P3227289697" "If you can find Jim before it's too late then he should listen to reason. You can only hope that he and Sidewinder didn't split up, otherwise it may be too late for the other."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P948835955" "Expose Steel Mountain's evil plot!"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P3536888811" "Jim isn't answering his phone and doesn't want to hear the truth. The only way to get through to him is going to be in person, and that means finding him inside that Freakshow warehouse."
// TaskTitle :
"P1933004661" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>An Unreturned Phone Call</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Vigilante Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P465339740" "You've tuned into Jim's radio frequency, but can't transmit to him. Already you can hear maneuvering orders being issued between Jim and Sidewinder. It looks like the operation is already underway and they've split up."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P1256543966" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>An Unreturned Phone Call</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Vigilante Mission</i></color></span><br><br>Steel Mountain's lies were exposed thank to your efforts. It is unfortunate that Jim Matherson had to die defending this villain, but the truth had to come out, and it was the best way to ensure that Sidewinder would side with you. The ends justify the means in this case. The citizens should thank you for being able to make the difficult calls and ensuring that anything and everything will be done to ensure their safety and the safety of those who protect them. Godspeed, Jim, godspeed."
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P4201283913" "You rescued Jim Matherson from the Freaks, convince him that Steel Mountain is betraying him."
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P1128763739" "Talk to Jim Matherson"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P2183755563" "Kill Jim Matherson"
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P79500159" "You rescued Sidewinder from the Freakshow, convince him that Steel Mountain has betrayed them."
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P3902994097" "Talk to Sidewinder"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P814404107" "Survive the Freakshow onslaught!"
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P3351634057" "The Freakshow are coming!"
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P1813598340" "Here come the Freaks!"
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P1137240458" "More Freaks Incoming!"
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P1738702370" "Who Let the Freaks Out!?"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptEnterMission 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - Objective 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P811550682" "<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>Sidewinder, this is Matherson. I've disarmed the perimeter explosives and made my way inside, the path should be clear now, over.<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.4 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor SlateBlue>This is Sidewinder. I'm preparing to breach the compound. Entering radio silence for zero-five minutes, over.<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>Copy that, Sidewinder... Wait... what's that? We've got company! Abort the breach, I need help now!<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.4 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>Freaks everywhere! I need backup! Sidewinder, are you there? Anyone!?"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P2074589631" "<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor SlateBlue>I'm in the compound, talk to me Matherson...<em>I've got Freaks all over the place, I'm in a tight spot, do you read? Over."
// Script Variable PET_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P3435277430" "Calm down there fellahs..."
// Script Variable PET_ACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P3702759070" "{HeroName}? Man am I glad to see you!"
