// RandomFameString :
"P3159570327" "I heard that {HeroName} stopped a Crey experiment that went berserk."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_VigToVil_SL6-7_Task_08 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - AllyConflictDialogue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P1129521154" "You've defeated Shadowphage! We... Ugh...!"
// Answer Text :
"P509596932" "Lance, what's wrong?"
// Page Page1 Text :
"P1736533566" "I... I don't know... My strength... It's... It's flooding back to me!"
// Answer Text :
"P2287536623" "Talk to me Lance, what's happening?"
// Page Page2 Text :
"P2526283895" "Oh... Oh no! No! NO!!! It... It's in my mind! {HeroName}... Help me... Don't let Shadowphage take me!"
// Answer Text :
"P3569345536" "Don't give into it, Lance. Fight it. Fight it!"
// Page Page3 Text :
"P2178049234" "...<br><br>...<br><br>Lance Hightower is now a prisoner inside his own body, {HeroName}. He no longer has any power that is not mine to command! Lance Hightower is no more, there is only Shadowphage!"
// Answer Text :
"P691538479" "If that's true then Lance is dead and his blood demands vengeance!"
// Page Page4 Text :
"P2262983018" "The only blood that will be spilled here today, {HeroName}... is yours!"
// Answer Text :
"P3318293876" "(Fight)"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - VillainConflictDialogue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P4062808270" "Ah ha ha ha ha... you are as powerful and ruthless as I had hoped, {HeroName}. You killed Lance off without a moment's hesitation, and for what? To deny me a body? A single body out of a wardrobe that I can don or discard as I please?<br><br>It wasn't vengeance, it was jealous rage! You and I both see the power of the other and crave it. We should join! We both seek to change the world. Together we'll bring 'justice' to the world, rebuild it as we see fit!<br><br>Admit it, this world needs to be cleansed. Join with me and you will decide who lives and who dies... Let the streets of your beloved Paragon City run red with justice."
// Answer Text :
"P1347351356" ""The only red you're going to see is the fires of hell!" (Kill Shadowphage)"
// Page FinishHim Text :
"P1229732055" "Ah ha ha ha ha ha! And I shall see you there soon enough!"
// Answer Text :
"P1476778464" "Tell them, {HeroName} sent you!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P3624149512" "Lance Hightower's disappearance has helped you pinpoint the location of the lair of the evil Nictus, Shadowphage. Shadowphage has been plaguing the Rogue Isles for some time, and its targeting of Arachnos and other big name villains was at first a boon, but then it started targeting Longbow and good guys like you. The real danger didn't become apparent until then, Shadowphage has been using the bodies of its victims as hosts for more of its kind. It plans to bring a Nictus army into this world in order to conquer us. Well not on your watch. There is only one cure for evil of this magnitude; death!"
// AcceptString :
"P3686515017" "Villain: Shadowphage cannot be allowed to live!"
// SendOffString :
"P2570233329" "You can only hope that Lance Hightower is still alive by the time you find your way into Shadowphage's subterranean lair. If he is, then he might just be tough enough to provide you with some much needed muscle against Shadowphage. That is, assuming he's in any condition to fight."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P2347724885" "Destroy Shadowphage's plans for world domination"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P3444869688" "Shadowphage isn't going anywhere. Find Lance Hightower. If he's still alive maybe he can lend you a hand in taking down this alien menace!"
// TaskTitle :
"P1616222491" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Old Fashioned Detective Work</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Vigilante Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P3444517888" "Nobody will stop you today. Shadowphage will die!"
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P385861628" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Old Fashioned Detective Work</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>If any of Lance Hightower was left inside him after Shadowphage took him over, then you did him a favor. The Nictus had already claimed his body, that much was clear, but nothing was going to stop you from finishing Shadowphage off when the chance presented itself, not even the chance that Lance could have been saved. Shadowphage was right, some humans are just worth more than others."
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P3730522435" "Lance Hightower wants to talk to you."
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P533478257" "Talk to Lance Hightower"
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P3565035820" "Confront Shadowphage and finish it off!"
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P3054006152" "Hear Shadowphage's last words"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P1272123933" "Defeat Shadowphage"
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P2616183117" "Defeat Lance Hightower!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptEnterMission 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P4090110553" "<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor SteelBlue> {HeroName}? No, not you too! Run! Escape while you still can!<t=10 caption x= 0.2 y=0.4 d=10><scale 1.75><color FireBrick><bgcolor Black>Ahhh, {HeroName}. I see you've come to rescue Mr. Hightower. I will never understand you humans and your need to save the more insignificant members of your species. Well, you are welcome to try, anyway!<t=3 caption x= 0.2 y=0.2 d=3><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor SteelBlue>Get out of here, {HeroName}... it's a t...<t=7 caption x= 0.2 y=0.4 d=4><scale 1.75><color FireBrick><bgcolor Black>Your defiance ends now, Lance Hightower. Your plea for help has left your mind open to me. And once I'm done with it... {HeroName} is next!"
// Script Variable HOSTAGE_NAME :
"P1735241713" "Lance Hightower"
// Script Variable HOSTAGE_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P1733094348" "You alien scum make me want to puke!"
// Script Variable HOSTAGE_ACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P3821632793" "Cavalry has arrived, alright!"
// Script Variable SayOnRescue :
"P1987841470" "Come on, we need to stop Shadowphage before it gets away!"
// Script Variable SayOnRecapture :
"P4170431104" "<shout>{HeroName}, I've got company!"
// Script Variable SayOnRerescue :
"P723551821" "Thanks, it means a lot to me."
// Script Variable SayOnStranded :
"P2577449648" "<shout>Whoa, slow down there, not all of us can resist having a donut in the mornings."
// Script Variable CAPTOR_NAME :
"P1547243976" "Nictus"
// Script Variable CAPTOR_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P3486843927" "Even so weakened this human is still resistant to my attempt to claim his form!"
// Script Variable CAPTOR_ACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P4266057393" "Perhaps {HeroName} will prove less resistant to my power!"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P3656576396" "I... I'm weak... Listen, we have very little time. We need to stop Shadowphage. Hopefully my strength will return soon."
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P865097367" "You've done it!"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P1771545501" "You cannot stop me without killing Hightower in the process, {HeroName}!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptHeroAllyRescued 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P2997805578" "Find Lance Hightower"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P3280078433" "Shadowphage"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P2238578612" "Shadowphage is a sinister Nictus intent on bringing an army of the dark entities into our world and conquering it. To do so, it needs powerful hosts for its Nictus brethren to reside within. Shadowphage must be stopped!"
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P389371970" "<shout>Finally, the brave {HeroName} is here, and with Lance Hightower in tow. You should have fled when you had the chance!"
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P2910157161" "Once I've obliterated your essence you too will become host to another one of my glorious people. You will join me in the conquest of this world and together we will destroy all that you once held so dear!"
// Script Variable BOSS_75HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P3156008187" "You will make excellent hosts."
// Script Variable BOSS_50HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P1947301192" "I may take you as a host myself. If you would just die!"
// Script Variable BOSS_25HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P948684660" "Alright... I yield! I yield..."
// Script Variable BOSS_KILLEDHERO_DIALOG :
"P1786169123" "None can oppose me, soon this pitiful world will be mine!"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P3064481301" "... Ha ha ha... You miserable fool! You haven't won! The fight has only begun!"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P3262127492" "Yes, become the monster that you so hate!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptVillainDefeated 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - TaskSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog :
"P3160620224" "You defeated the evil Nictus known as Shadowphage, but it claimed the life of Lance Hightower. Casualties are a reality of war... And this is a war. If good is to triumph over evil, it will be at the cost of brave good men like Lance Hightower."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - ReturnSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// RandomFameString :
"P3219542485" "I heard that Lance Hightower died helping {HeroName} defeated that alien menace, Shadowphage."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_VigToVil_SL6-7_Task_09 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - ColonelsAccessCode 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P4286431382" "Instructor Molke's Password"
// DetailString :
"P4075191496" "The password to get into the computer system is as obvious as it is stupid; PARADE."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - NemesisAttackPlans 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P4058048006" "Fake Nemesis Attack Plan"
// DetailString :
"P3951124663" "This is the fake attack plan that you drafted up for the Nemesis Army to follow during tomorrow's parade. All you need to do is plant them on the body of the acting commander and let the chain of command carry your orders on to the condemnation of every soldier involved."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - SecurityTerminalDialogue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P1589777732" ""Welcome to the Nemesis Parade Planning Committee: Remember, see the sunshine in every day."<br><br><color orange>Wow... How, very cheery... Moving on."
// Answer Text :
"P3966389638" "Review parade plans"
// Answer Text :
"P2471435469" "Print out fake plans"
// Answer Text :
"P2498810942" "Locate the unit commander"
// Page NoAccess Text :
"P1026622380" "Incorrect Password: Please talk to Instructor Molke to review the parade plans"
// Answer Text :
"P759420227" "Molke... Right. One second..."
// Page ReviewParadePlans Text :
"P2512809547" ""Password Accepted"<br><br><color orange>The computer pulls up a fairly elaborate breakdown of the parade and all personnel in attendance, right down to the amount of confetti to be released. You see the parade structure, unit break downs, drills, and music for the event.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P1976938918" "Modify the parade plans"
// Page AccessSecurityFootage Text :
"P304143029" "<color orange>You modify the plans so that instead of what appears to be a standard parade rifle drill is instead a complex maneuver that ends in a two rank volley fire attack on the crowd. It is cleverly disguised and designed to inflict massive casualties on anyone stupid enough to actually be watching the parade.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P2563702099" "Print the plans"
// Page PrintFakePlans Text :
"P3228353079" "<color orange>You print out the plans, fold them, and then erase all traces of your tampering with the plans. The last bit of information you need is to find out who is in charge of this ludicrous farce!</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P1824995743" "Locate the commander of this parade unit"
// Page LocateLeader Text :
"P2494420337" "<color orange>You review the unit's hierarchy and discover that Colonel Wilhelm is in charge. You'll need to plant the fake plans on his body, so that when his men find him they'll read the plan, assume it came from Nemesis, and adopt it as their true mission.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P2466075353" "Log out of the computer"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P2162475682" "Waiting around on Nemesis's terms is idiotic, you need to act now if you hope to stop the coming bloodshed. Laws be damned, you're going into that Nemesis Parade Committee's office and you're going to find out what they're up to. You don't think you'll find anything, Nemesis is too smart for that, but something has to be done. Anything! If you can't find suitable evidence, then you just might have to plant your own."
// AcceptString :
"P3750643583" "Villain: I don't need evidence to prove that you're rotten, Nemesis."
// SendOffString :
"P3738569234" "They may appear to be setting up for a parade, but you know that those Nemesis soldiers are packing firepower. Storming into a community office filled with them is not going to be a picnic. But nobody else seems to be stepping up, so it looks like it's up to you to stop the latest Nemesis plot before 'Brass Sunday' begins."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P4042662351" "Find out what Nemesis is up to"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P1773259896" "Nemesis is notorious for hiding his true motives. If you can't find any evidence to convince the heroes of Paragon City to stop the parade, then you'll just have to plant some of your own. Too many lives are at stake for you to worry about the legitimacy of your good deeds!"
// TaskTitle :
"P1330947530" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Proper Documents</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Vigilante Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P48008155" "You can hear the clip-clap of boots on cement, the Nemesis soldiers are practicing for tomorrow's parade. If you have your way, then half of them are going to need crutches."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P1358247109" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Proper Documents</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Vigilante Mission</i></color></span><br><br>That went extremely well. The Nemesis Army will take the fake battle plan and carry it out in memory of their beloved colonel. When they open fire on the crowd, the assembled heroes will quickly neutralize them. Most importantly, whatever Nemesis was plotting will be foiled! Apparently not every Nemesis plot is actually his."
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P2913734172" "Access the Nemesis computer system"
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P3320005476" "You printed out your modified attack plans for tomorrow's Nemesis Army Parade, now to plant them on Colonel Wilhelm."
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P624864538" "Colonel Wilhelm's armor is reconstituting!"
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P2381908150" "Colonel Wilhelm is regenerating!"
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P2441459623" "Colonel Wilhelm has called for reinforcements!"
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P2965404695" "Reinforcements Incoming!"
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P2125873698" "Colonel Wilhelm's clockwork heart and lungs are keeping him alive!"
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P284424001" "Colonel Wilhelm continues to regenerate!"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P3578972611" "Instructor Moltke"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P797850300" "Instructor Moltke has finally found his calling in the Nemesis Army. Always with an eye for precision and presentation, Moltke has been tasked with drilling the Nemesis soldiers in proper parade maneuvers."
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P1966818214" "<shout>Hup! Hup! Hup Hup Hup!<em>Long! Live! Lord Neme-sis!<em> Hup! Hup! Hup... Halt!<em>No! Left, right, then left again! Are you daft!?"
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P2735413863" "Intruder!<em>Seize {Hero.gender=male him|her}!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptFirstBossDefeated 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P2688882628" "Defeat Instructor Moltke"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - Objective 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog :
"P3293819909" "You've acquired the password need to access the computer system from Molke. Once inside you can modify the parade plan and turn it into an attack plan."
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P1850530454" "Computer System"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P2692146251" "This computer contains all the information about the Nemesis Army Parade Committee's plans."
// Script Variable Greeting :
"P2788814047" "Welcome."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptSecurityTerminalUsed 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - Objective 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P3685614743" "Colonel Wilhelm"
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P4068612151" "<shout>We have a perimeter breach!<em>Everyone to your combat positions!<em>Prepare to meet the enemy in glorious combat!"
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P4133845533" "There {Hero.gender=male he|she} is! It's {HeroName}! VOLLEY FIRE!"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P2976771187" "My reactive armor has blunted your assault, {HeroName}1 Even now my uniform restitches itself to repel your feeble attacks!"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P235204304" "Rally to me, men! Rally to me!"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P3788651967" "Ha-ha! Praise Lord Nemesis! My auto-heart and internal respirators have kicked in, there's no stopping me now!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptSecondBossDefeated 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P2712368920" "Defeat Colonel Wilhelm"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - Objective 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog :
"P3622837624" "You planted the modified Nemesis Parade plans on Colonel Wilhelm's body. When his men find him they will carry out what they believe to be his final orders at tomorrow's parade and incriminate themselves, justifying all those who doubted the sincerity of Nemesis and his army!"
// Script Variable INACTIVE_DIALOG_MINION1 :
"P4111071479" "<shout>Quickly, the Colonel needs help!"
// Script Variable ATTACK_DIALOG_MINION1 :
"P1623958821" "It's {HeroName}! Attack!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - TaskSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog :
"P3386970865" "You successfully framed the Nemesis Army, ensuring that whatever their true plans were did not unfold. Innocents will certainly die, but you are certain that their deaths prevented countless more."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - ReturnSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// RandomFameString :
"P2117967319" "Hey, are you going to watch the Brass Sunday parade, {HeroName}?"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_VigToVil_SL6-7_Task_10 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - HeroDialogueTree 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P2985410424" "{HeroName}! You... You killed them... You destroyed them forever! You can't go around doing that, they're people too. We need to bring them into custody."
// Answer Text :
"P888799271" "Custody? They were about to kill you!"
// Answer Text :
"P2652385013" "The Circle deals in absolutes. Show them mercy and you receive death."
// Answer Text :
"P3152406393" "This is what happens to those who show mercy to the wicked."
// Page TooLenient Text :
"P3700752497" "True, but as a hero I face dangers like this all the time. It is my job to bring villains such as the Circle to justice before a court of law."
// Answer Text :
"P1644933052" "Law? The only law the Circle recognizes is death!"
// Page TooLenient2 Text :
"P3437352391" "Death? I'll not kill the Circle, {HeroName}. Villains that they are, they are still people, and still deserve to be shown mercy. To deny them this is to be no different than them."
// Answer Text :
"P1534659030" "You're wrong. They kill for themselves. I kill for the greater good."
// Page TryingAgain Text :
"P118867871" "You cannot convince me, {HeroName}. We need to work together and destroy that altar. Alright?"
// Answer Text :
"P3296787877" "So, an evil altar you can destroy, but not those who built it?"
// Page TeachingALesson Text :
"P2666413080" "Wh... Why are you doing this? Didn't you hear that wizard? If I am sacrificed upon this altar then a great evil will come into this world!"
// Answer Text :
"P2591860928" "I'm not going to kill you, but you'll see what your mercy would allow."
// Page TeachingALesson2 Text :
"P2750157587" "<color orange>You end the ritual prematurely, freeing Sarah Winters from the Altar of Darkness.</color><br><br>"I... I can't believe you would do that to me just to try and make a point! {HeroName}, you are better than this! You can't deal in such absolutes. What you're suggesting is that evil deeds can only be dealt with by other evil deeds. I cannot believe that! If I gave into such beliefs then what hope would there be for the world?""
// Answer Text :
"P3874573391" "There can be no hope without victory. What good is hope if you are dead?"
// Page TeachingALesson3 Text :
"P4277837001" "Victory at the expense of all that we fight for is just as good as letting evil win. {HeroName}, I fear that you have lost your way and are now walking down a path of darkness! I cannot, in good conscious, allow you to continue to fight with evil. I want you to surrender yourself to me so I can get you some help."
// Answer Text :
"P2887372260" "You want me to surrender when I'm the one winning the war!?"
// Page TeachingALesson4 Text :
"P243556553" "The war you are fighting is in the name of evil, {HeroName}. I'm sorry that you cannot see this, but, I must stop you in the hopes that you can be redeemed."
// Answer Text :
"P1563563856" "Redemption is what my enemies beg for before they die! Time to beg!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P3425358612" "Sarah Winters, a Longbow Officer you know to have a personal vendetta against the Circle of Thorns, is taking on the Circle in a one woman war against them. Your hope is that her loyalty to Longbow won't prevent her from doing what needs to be done against these murderous cultists."
// AcceptString :
"P2988617182" "Vigilante: Now is the time for Sarah Winters to finally make a difference."
// SendOffString :
"P597859899" "Sarah Winters needs to learn to embrace her hatred of the Circle and deal with them in absolutes. The Circle cares not for our laws, so our laws should not be applied to them."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P1338803654" "Help Sarah Winters destroy the Circle"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P4190576285" "You need to show Sarah Winters the only way to deal with the Circle of Thorns!"
// TaskTitle :
"P2168063078" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Warm Brass and Cold Bodies</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Vigilante Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P4019392364" "Sarah Winter's hatred of the Circle has gotten the better of her, she's proceeded into the fray without backup. This is promising."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P4252821085" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Warm Brass and Cold Bodies</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color slategray><i>Vigilante Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You showed Sarah Winters how to deal best with the Circle of Thorns, and indeed, all villains. Even though the Circle wasn't willing to show her mercy, she was incapable of being as merciless as them. You had to show Sarah Winters the error of her ways, but she wouldn't listen. When did the heroes start defending evil doers?! You still don't understand what she was thinking, trying to stay your hand from striking the Circle down. But it matters no more, nobody will stand in the way of justice, not even a coward who is incapable of doing what needs to be done against the vermin of this world!"
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P2621582964" "You rescued Sarah Winters from the Circle. Show her that the Circle is undeserving and incapable of mercy."
// Script Variable FloaterMessage :
"P1772778370" "Speak to Sarah Winters"
// Script Variable ChatMessage :
"P4123947864" "With Sarah Winters incapacitated, you will show her how great of a weakness mercy truly is."
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P180064261" "Defeat Sarah Winters"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptEnterMission 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P515551191" "<t=5 caption x= 0.2 y=0.4 d=4><scale 1.75><color white><bgcolor FireBrick>First Sarah Winters... and now {HeroName}. The prophecy has come true! Now all that remains is your sacrifice to bring about a great evil into this world!"
// Script Variable HOSTAGE_NAME :
"P2481715923" "Sarah Winters"
// Script Variable HOSTAGE_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P1046370391" "This could go badly..."
